[Event "Wijk aan Zee"]
[Site "Wijk aan Zee"]
[Date "2013.01.15"]
[White "Levon Aronian"]
[Black "Viswanathan Anand"]
[Result "0-1"]
[Blurb "A modern immortal. Anand, then World Champion, uncorks a stunning piece sacrifice out of a quiet Semi-Slav — the black pieces flood in and the whole attack is worked out to the end."]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 Nbd7 6. Bd3 dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 8. Bd3 Bd6 9. O-O O-O 10. Qc2 Bb7 11. a3 Rc8
12. Ng5 {White lunges at h7 — but Anand has seen further.} c5 13. Nxh7 Ng4 {Ignoring the lost pawn; the knight heads for the kingside.}
14. f4 cxd4 15. exd4 Bc5 16. Be2 Nde5 {A second knight joins, both eyeing the white king.}
17. Bxg4 Bxd4+ 18. Kh1 Nxg4 19. Nxf8 f5 {Anand gives back the exchange to keep every attacking piece on the board.}
20. Ng6 Qf6 21. h3 Qxg6 22. Qe2 Qh5 23. Qd3 Be3 {White resigned — the threats of ...Bxf4 and ...Qxh3+ are unstoppable. A masterpiece of calculation.}
